 Educational Background



BTECH in Civil Engineering 


Indian Institute of Technology Madras

                  The Indian Institute of Technology, Madras, is among the foremost of institutes of national importance in higher technological education and in basic and applied research. The Institute, with nearly 360 faculty, 4000 students, 1250 administrative and supporting staff, is a self-contained campus  and is located in a beautiful, wooded land of about 250 hectares in South Madras                




MBA in Finance 


Simon Business School

                  At Simon Business School, we offer an education that will attract students who value our analytic bias.                





 Career History



Product Manager

                                    2009 - Current                


Grantham, Mayo, Van Otterloo & Co. LLC


                  GMO, founded in 1977, is a privately held global investment management firm servicing clients in the corporate, public, endowment, and foundation marketplaces. As of December 31, 2012, we managed $106 billion* in client assets using a blend of traditional judgments with innovative quantitative methods to find undervalued securities and markets.

Our success in consistently providing value added performance across a broad range of asset classes is founded on several key factors that include: discipline, value orientation, investment research, and constant innovation (see GMO Qualities below). Our broad-based value added over benchmarks has led many of our clients to request that we allocate assets and advise them on a global scale                




Advanced Strategies & Research Group

                                    Prior                


Barclays Global Investors NA






Portfolio Manager

                                    Prior - 2008                


AXA Rosenberg Investment Management LLC


                  AXA Rosenberg Investment Management provides investment management services based on fundamental equity analysis using quantitative methods. The firm's investment approach is driven by bottom-up stock selection based on the rigorous fundamental analysis of company valuations and earnings combined with an understanding of both the stock specific and environmental risks that accompany this approach. AXA Rosenberg’s approach is applied globally and is implemented locally by experienced investment teams based in the US, Europe and Asia to create broadly diversified portfolios with a range of objectives from active equities (including enhanced index, large cap, small cap and “defensive equity income” type strategies) and \"\"SmartBeta\"\" strategies. The firm primarily invests in common stocks traded on the principal exchanges of major markets. The use of derivatives is currently not a strategic part of their investment approach. However, their goal is to be fully invested in equities at all times. As permitted, AXA Rosenberg may use stock index futures or ETFs to overlay cash or accruals and obtain exposure to the equity markets.                




Investment Strategist

                                    Prior                


BlackRock Fund Advisors


                  BlackRock Fund Advisors offers active, enhanced and index strategies across markets and asset classes. The firm's products are offered in a variety of structures including separate accounts, mutual funds, iShares (ETFs) and other pooled investment vehicles. BlackRock Fund Advisors also offers risk management, advisory and enterprise investment system services to institutional investors through BlackRock Solutions.                





